  "prompt": "Is Masters in Public Health course included in SOL?",
  "response": "The Status of Overseas Learning (SOL) can vary by country and institution, so it's essential to clarify which country or educational system you are referring to when asking about the inclusion of a Masters in Public Health (MPH) in the SOL. Generally, in countries like Australia, the Skilled Occupation List (SOL) includes courses and professions that are in demand and may allow for certain pathways for work and visas.\n\nIn Australia, for example, public health professionals may be listed in the SOL or the Consolidated Sponsored Occupations List (CSOL), highlighting the need for these professionals.\n\nTo get the most accurate and updated information, it's best to check the official immigration or education websites of the relevant country or contact the educational institution you are interested in. If you have a specific country in mind, please let me know!",
